<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,599,1457,1482]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289">
Description of the male 
<typeStatus box="[489,594,1458,1481]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[762,846,1457,1481]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="289" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
. Wing length: 
<quantity box="[1014,1117,1457,1481]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="3" pageNumber="289" unit="mm" value="11.5">11.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1129,1193,1458,1481]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1209,1281,1457,1482]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1149,1170]" captionTargetBox="[192,1393,193,1115]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[189,1394,193,1116]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head. A – B Palpada panorama sp. n. male (holotype). A. frontal view; B. lateral view. C – D Palpada erratica Curran, male (Peru, Pucallpa, 23. iv. 1965, J. Schunke, BMNH). C. frontal view; D. lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259146/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="289">
Figs 
<number box="[1267,1281,1457,1481]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B; 
<number box="[1351,1364,1457,1481]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289" value="3.0">3</number>
A, B). Face shiny black, densely silver white pollinose and pilose, except for bare medial vitta of approximately 
<number box="[1368,1377,1493,1518]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1388,1404,1493,1518]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289" value="4.0">4</number>
of facial width. Antenna dark brown; basoflagellomere approximately 
<number box="[923,957,1529,1553]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289" value="1.5">1.5</number>
x as long as wide; arista pale brown, very short and thinly pubescent. Lunule brownish. Frontal triangle shiny black, except narrowly silver white pollinose along eye margins; black pilose medially, white pilose laterally. Vertical triangle black; black pilose and pollinose, except white pollinose before anterior ocellus. Ocelli orange; frontal angle approximately 
<number box="[1210,1242,1637,1661]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289" value="60.0">60</number>
°. Holoptic; ratio length of frons / length of eye contiguity = 
<number box="[631,646,1673,1698]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289" value="7.0">7</number>
/ 
<number box="[656,671,1673,1698]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289" value="9.0">9</number>
. Eye with strongly enlarged ommatidia in dorsal half, conspicuously larger than in ventral half; nine of the largest ommatidia together are about as wide as the lunule; pale pilose on dorsal half. Gena black. Occiput silver white pilose and pollinose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[927,1016,1746,1769]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1034,1100,1745,1770]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1893,1914]" captionTargetBox="[174,1424,438,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1868]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Palpada panorama sp. n. male. A. Holotype, dorsal view; B. Holotype, lateral view; C. Paratype (from Suriname), dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259145/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="289">
Fig. 
<number box="[1089,1100,1745,1770]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Postpronotum black; black pilose. Mesoscutum black with three wide, silver grey fasciae: along anterior margin, along of transverse suture, and just before posterior margin; short black pilose. Postalar callus black; black pilose, except for some long pale pile anterolaterally. Scutellum yellow with anterior margin black; short black pilose, longer on posterior margin. Pleuron black; greyish white pollinose and white pilose, except black pollinose and bare on anterior part of anepisternum, black pollinose and black pilose on anterior anepimeron, bare on dorsomedial anepimeron; meron bare. Metasternum black, long white pilose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[650,713,1962,1985]" pageId="3" pageNumber="289">Legs.</emphasis>
Coxae black; silver white pollinose, white pilose, except medial coxae with some sparse brownish pile anteriorly. Trochanters black, white pollinose, brownish pilose anteriorly, white pilose posteriorly. Femora black, except narrowly brownish at apex; white pilose, except brownish pilose apicodorsally. Tibiae reddish brown; white pilose basodorsally, brownish pilose apicodorsally, brownish golden pilose ventrally. Tarsi reddish brown; black pilose dorsally, brownish golden pilose ventrally. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1245,1310,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1329,1399,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,588,609]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,566]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,566]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Basal wing cells. A. Palpada panorama sp. n., male (holotype); B. Palpada erratica (Curran), male (Peru, Pucallpa, 23. iv. 1965, J. Schunke, BMNH)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259148/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="290">
Fig. 
<number box="[1385,1399,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Hyaline. Microtrichose, except bare of microtrichia on basal 
<number box="[830,842,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[851,866,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="4.0">4</number>
of cell c, basal 
<number box="[1039,1049,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1060,1075,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="3.0">3</number>
of r 
<number box="[1125,1136,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="1.0">1</number>
, basal 
<number box="[1212,1226,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1236,1248,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="3.0">3</number>
of r, basal 
<number box="[1370,1384,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="4.0">4</number>
/ 
<number box="[1394,1406,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="5.0">5</number>
of bm, basal 
<number box="[266,279,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[288,301,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="5.0">5</number>
of cup, basal 
<number box="[459,469,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[479,495,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="2.0">2</number>
of anal lobe and basomedian 
<number box="[831,841,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[851,867,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="2.0">2</number>
of alula. Calypter white with dark brown margins. Halter yellowish. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[357,474,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[492,559,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1893,1914]" captionTargetBox="[174,1424,438,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,411,1868]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Palpada panorama sp. n. male. A. Holotype, dorsal view; B. Holotype, lateral view; C. Paratype (from Suriname), dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259145/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="290">
Fig. 
<number box="[548,559,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Terga black, except for pairs of large yellow maculae on terga II and III. Tergum IV with medially interrupted steely blue fascia. Short black pilose, except long white pilose on anterolateral corner of tergum I and along lateral margins of terga II, III and IV. Sterna I and IV black, sterna II and III yellow, white pilose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[424,535,439,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[550,614,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1392,1413]" captionTargetBox="[159,1432,694,1366]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,690,1370]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia, lateral view. A. Palpada panorama sp. n. (paratype from Peru); B. Palpada erratica (Curran) (Brazil, Rondônia, Ouro Preto d´Oeste, 20. xi. 1987, leg. C. Elias, coll. DZUP)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259149/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="290">
Fig. 
<number box="[602,614,439,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="290" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Epandrium narrow on dorsal portion; with ventral and dorsal margins proportionally similar; surstylus, in lateral view, with ventral margin slightly convex, anterodorsal and dorsal margins slightly concave; apical half of the hypandrium elongated and straight relative to basal half, without ctenidia; aedeagus convex dorsally, apex of the lobe tapered, shorter than width of the anterior half.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
